Two things and the second is probably much more important than the first but is getting little mention;

1) I'm in two minds with Mitch McConnell, it would be nice to see his face if the voters of Kentucky kicked him out of office just to watch him squirm and complain would be good to watch. But if the Democrats could take the Senate and McConnell retain his seat, it would also be really sweet to watch him sit in the Senate and watch the Democrats pass legislation using all of the new rules he has introduced or amended. To watch the Democrats get rid of the 60-40 rule on all matters and go to a simple majority and in the debate to use McConnell as the point of reference for doing it. To pass legislation and if Trump somehow retains office and then veto's to use their veto override to make it law. To reign in the right of the President to make executive orders to the pre Ford levels and to fast track Washington DC, Puerto Rico and the US Virgin Islands which would all be blue States that would return six Democratic Senators to the Senate making it so much harder for the Republicans to ever regain the Senate.

2) Somehow in all the debate about Trump it appears to have passed a lot of people's notice that 2021 is a census year and whoever controls the State Legislators will be in a position to redraw many electoral boundaries. for twenty five years the Republicans have been gerrymandering the districts and if the Democrats can win back seats in State Legislators so they have the majorities they will be able in the next few years to wipe out thirty or so years of Republican gerrymandering. People need to make sure they vote all the way down the ticket because this is the last chance for ten years to reshape the electoral map of the US.
